-- Baker & McKenzie Hires Ex-Mayer Partner Chris Horn for Securities Practice
-- B y   I a n   T h o m a s
-- 2012-02-21T17:18:37Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-21/baker-mckenzie-hires-ex-mayer-partner-chris-horn-for-securities-practice.html
Baker & McKenzie LLP (1111L)  hired
Christopher Horn, a partner at  Mayer Brown LLP (1120L) , to boost its
structured finance practice.  Horn, 41, has experience in the securitization and
financing of auto loans and leases,  Baker & McKenzie  said today
in an e-mailed statement. Horn will join the firm’s New York
office as a partner on its banking and finance team.  “We are expanding our capabilities for clients in the
finance area, and his significant experience in securitization
and structured finance matters will be a great asset to both our
financial institution and corporate clients,” James C. Colihan,
managing partner of the firm’s New York office, said in the
statement.  Baker & McKenzie is an international firm with more than
3,800 lawyers. It was ranked the highest-grossing  law firm  in
fiscal 2010 with revenue of $2.1 billion,  according  to the
American Lawyer, a trade publication.  To contact the reporter on this story:
